I bought five Border Leicester ewe lambs (four months old) in July. I had that summer to learn about grazing and handling them, a winter feeding hay, and a second summer of grazing. In fall, their second year, they were bred, lambing the next spring. I paid to use a Coopworth ram to service the ewes for the first two breeding years. That way I did not have to keep two separate groups of sheep, rams and ewes. \
